{The Maroczy Bind is one of chess's most fundamental pawn structures. Many different openings can reach it. Mastering this pawn structure, you will improve your chess understanding in general.} 1. e4 (1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 g6 6. e4) (1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. Be2 c5 7. O-O cxd4 8. Nxd4) 1... c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 (2... d6 3. Bb5+ Bd7 4. Bxd7+ Qxd7 5. c4 {This is slightly different from Maroczy's setup with the light-squared bishop exchanged. This is strategically good for White. On the other hand, with one minor piece exchanged, Black can breathe easier.}) 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6 5. c4 Bg7 6. Be3 *

