{[#]} 19. cxb5 Bh6 $3 {Very nice tactical resource. Black is exchanging the light-squared bishops.} 20. Bf1 (20. Bxh6 $4 Nd3+) 20... Bxe3+ 21. Qxe3 Na4 22. Qxb6 Nxb6 {[%csl Rb6,Yf1] We get one of the most favorable endgames for Black.} 23. a4 Kf8 {Now Black plays practically with a pawn up. His plan is simply to push his central pawns.} 24. Kf2 Ke8 25. Ke3 Kd7 26. Bd3 e6 27. Kd2 d5 28. e5 $6 (28. f4 {was the better defence}) 28... Kd8 {[%csl Rd5] Now Black has a protected passed pawn.} 29. f4 Nd7 {[%csl Rb6,Rc7,Rd8][%cal Rc8c5]} 30. Rxc8+ Rxc8 31. Bc2 Kc7 32. Rf1 Kb6 33. Rf3 h5 34. g3 d4 {The most convincing way to convert the advantage.} 35. Bd1 Kc5 36. Rd3 Nb6 37. Bf3 Nd5 38. Ke2 (38. Bxd5 {doesn't help, because the pawn endgame is simply lost.} Kxd5) 38... h4 $1 {opening the second front} 39. Rd2 hxg3 40. hxg3 Rh8 $19 {Now it is over.} 41. Bg2 b6 42. Kd3 Ne3 43. Bc6 Rh3 44. Rf2 Rxg3 45. Rf3 Rxf3 46. Bxf3 Nd5 47. Ke4 Kb4 48. Kxd4 Nxf4 49. Bd1 g5 50. Bc2 g4 51. Ke3 g3 52. Kf3 g2 53. Kf2 Kc3 0-1

