1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. c4 Nc6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nf6 6. Nc3 d6 7. Be2 Nxd4 8. Qxd4 Bg7 9. Be3 O-O 10. Qd2 a5 {I like this concept. White can't stop a5-a4. Black wins some space on the queenside and then simply attacks the pawn on c4. Black's play is much easier, in my opinion. Of course, White investigated this position and tried different ways to get an advantage, but still the ball was in their court.} 11. f3 a4 12. Rc1 (12. O-O Be6 13. Rab1 Qa5 14. b4 axb3 15. axb3 Qb4 {0-1 Savanovic,A (2410)-Mekhitarian,K (2554) Titled Tuesday intern op 19th May Chess.com INT blitz 2020 (3) Black's position is already very comfortable.}) 12... Qa5 13. Kf2 $5 (13. Rc2 Bd7 14. g4 Bc6 15. Nd5 (15. h4 h5) 15... Nxd5 16. cxd5 Bb5) (13. O-O {is quite harmless due to the following forcing line} Be6 14. Nd5 Qxd2 15. Nxe7+ (15. Bxd2) 15... Kh8 16. Bxd2 Rfe8 17. Nd5 Nxd5 18. cxd5 Bxd5 19. Bb5 Re5 20. Bc3 (20. exd5 Rxd5 $11) 20... Bxa2 $17 {This line is really important; everyone should know it by heart.}) 13... Be6 14. Nd5 Bxd5 ({after:} 14... Nxd5 $6 15. Qxa5 Rxa5 16. cxd5 Bd7 (16... Bc8 $1 $14) 17. Rc7 $1 $18) (14... Qxd2 $2 15. Nxe7+ $1 Kh8 16. Bxd2 Rfe8 17. Nd5 {The e2-bishop is protected and Black has no compensation for the sacrificing material.}) 15. Qxa5 Rxa5 16. cxd5 (16. exd5 Nd7 17. Rb1 Nc5 18. Rhd1 f5 19. g3 Raa8 $11) 16... e6 $1 {With the king on f2, this move is very strong} 17. Bd2 (17. Bf4 exd5 18. Bxd6 Re8 (18... dxe4 19. Bxf8 Bxf8 20. Rhd1) 19. Bc7 b6 $1 $13) (17. dxe6 fxe6 18. Ke1 {White needs to spent another tempo to remove the king from the f-file} Nd7 19. Rc2 Ne5 $1 20. Bd2 Rc5 21. Rxc5 dxc5 22. f4 Nc6 $11) 17... Raa8 18. Bb4 exd5 19. e5 (19. Bxd6 Rfd8 20. Be7 Rd7 21. Bxf6 Bxf6 22. Rhd1 Bxb2 23. Rc2 $11) 19... dxe5 $1 20. Bxf8 Bxf8 {Even though the position is objectively equal. In a practical game Black's game is much easier and he went to win the game.} 21. a3 b6 22. Rc6 $6 Bc5+ 23. Ke1 Nh5 $1 24. g3 Ng7 $1 25. Rc7 Rd8 $6 26. Kd2 f5 27. Ba6 $6 Ne6 28. Rc8 Rxc8 29. Bxc8 Nd4 30. Rf1 Kf7 31. Bd7 b5 32. Bc8 Ke7 33. Kd3 Kd6 34. h4 e4+ 35. fxe4 fxe4+ 36. Kd2 Nb3+ 37. Ke2 d4 38. Bb7 d3+ 39. Ke1 e3 40. Be4 Nc1 $1 41. Bxd3 Nxd3+ 42. Ke2 Nxb2 43. Rf6+ Kd5 44. Rf7 Bxa3 45. Rxh7 Bc5 46. Rg7 a3 47. Rxg6 a2 48. Rg5+ Kc4 49. Rg4+ Bd4 0-1

