1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6 5. c4 Bg7 6. Nc3 Nf6 7. Be3 d6 8. Be2 O-O 9. O-O Bd7 10. h3 {[%csl Bh3] A modern idea with multiple purposes. It controls the g4 square, does not weaken the g1-a7 diagonal and allows a possible Bg4 in some lines.} (10. Qd2 Nxd4 11. Bxd4 Bc6 12. f3 a5 13. b3 Nd7 14. Be3 Nc5 15. Rab1 e6) 10... Nxd4 11. Bxd4 Bc6 12. Qc2 a5 13. Rad1 {[%csl Rd8][%cal Gd1d8]} a4 $5 {[%cal Bd8a5] Our recommendation. An attractive approach with the purpose to tactically complicate the game, giving it an active, classically Sicilian character.} (13... Nd7 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. Bg4 {[%csl Rd7][%cal Gg4d7,Ge4e5,Gc4c5]} Ne5 (15... Nc5 16. e5 $16) 16. c5 $1 {This is another benefit of 10.h3. The bishop on g4 is defended and White, without wasting time, can advance his c-pawn.} Nxg4 (16... b5 $5) 17. hxg4 Qc8 18. cxd6 Qxg4 19. dxe7 Rfe8 20. Nd5 $1 Bxd5 21. Qc3+ Kg8 22. exd5 Rxe7 23. Rd4 (23. d6 $1 Rd7 24. Rfe1 Qg5 25. Re3 Qd8 26. Qe5 {With a more active piece arrangement for White than in the game.}) 23... Qc8 24. Qd2 Qf5 25. d6 Rd7 26. Rd5 Qf6 27. Rd1 a4 $14 {[%csl Bd6] 1-0 Firouzja,A (2728) -Vachier Lagrave,M (2778)/chess.com INT 2020/Mega2020}) 14. c5 (14. Rfe1 {does not cause any problems.} Qa5 15. Bf3 Nd7 16. Bxg7 Kxg7 {[%csl Rf3] White's bishop on f3 is a clumsy piece.} 17. Bg4 Ne5 18. Nd5 (18. Be2 Rfc8 19. Qd2 Qc5 {[%csl Rc4][%cal Ga4b3,Ga8a3,Ge5c4]}) 18... e6 $5 {A fierce move, looking for a complex game.} (18... Bxd5 19. exd5 Qc5 20. Qc3 (20. b3 $6 b5 $1 $36) 20... Qxc4 21. Qxc4 Nxc4 22. Rxe7 Nxb2 23. Rb1 a3 24. Rxb7 h5 25. Be2 Na4 $13 {[%cal Ga4c5,Ga4c3] Arriving at a complex endgame, where Black's chances are at least equal.}) 19. Ne3 f5 20. exf5 gxf5 21. Bxf5 $4 (21. Be2 f4 22. Ng4 f3 $15) (21. Bh5 $5 {Interestingly, a possible line is} Kh8 22. f4 Be4 23. Qe2 Nd7 24. Rxd6 Nf6 25. Red1 Qc5 26. Kh2 Nxh5 27. Qxh5 Qxe3 28. Rd7 Qxf4+ 29. Kg1 Qe3+ 30. Kh2) 21... exf5 22. Nxf5+ Rxf5 23. Qxf5 Nf3+ {0-1 Berger Dit Lacroix,K (2114) -Shevchenko,K (2605)/ Europe-Echecs INT 2021}) 14... Qa5 $1 {As a consequence of 13...a4, Black is left with a weak pawn on d6 in exchange for active play for his pieces.} 15. cxd6 exd6 16. a3 (16. Bc4 {The bishop is not well placed on this square due to the constant pressure against the e4-pawn.} Rfe8 $1 {[%csl Be4] The best move, offering excellent counterplay for Black.} (16... Nxe4 $5 {This tactical resource is playable, although it does not achieve complete equality.} 17. Bxg7 (17. Nxe4 d5 18. Nf6+ Bxf6 19. Bxf6 dxc4 20. Rd6 $14) 17... Kxg7 18. Nxe4 d5 19. b4 $1 axb3 20. Qb2+ f6 21. Nxf6 Rxf6 22. Bxb3 $14) 17. Rfe1 (17. f3 b5 $1 18. Be2 b4 19. Nb1 {[%csl Rb1]} Rac8 20. Qd2 (20. Qd3 $2 Nxe4 21. fxe4 Bxe4 $17 {[%csl Re2][%cal Ge4b1,Ge8e2]}) 20... d5 $1 21. e5 Nh5 22. f4 Ng3 $132 {[%cal Gg3f5]}) 17... b5 $1 18. Bf1 b4 $132 {[%cal Ga8c8,Gc6e4]} 19. Bxf6 (19. Ne2 $6 Bxe4 $15 (19... Rac8 $5 $36)) 19... Bxf6 20. Rxd6 bxc3 21. Rxf6 cxb2 {[%csl Be1]} 22. Rd1 Bxe4 23. Qxb2) 16... Rfe8 17. Bf3 (17. Bd3 {is a little bit better.} Nh5 (17... d5 $2 {White is well placed for this central reaction.} 18. e5 Ne4 (18... Nh5 $2 19. f4 $16) 19. f4 $16) (17... Re6 18. Rfe1 Rae8 19. Qd2 {With a very tense position.}) 18. Bxg7 Kxg7 19. Rfe1 Nf6 20. f3 Qb6+ 21. Qf2 Qxf2+ 22. Kxf2 d5 23. e5 Nd7 24. f4 Nc5 25. Bb1 Red8 26. Ne2 Ra6 27. Nd4 Rb6 {With possibilities for both sides.}) 17... Re6 $1 {Planning to double rooks on the e-file and press against the weak e4-pawn. Black is perfectly fine!} 18. Nd5 $6 (18. Rfe1 Rae8 19. Re2 h5 20. g3 b5 $1 $132) 18... Bxd5 19. exd5 Ree8 {This transformation of the pawn structure favours Black.} 20. Bc3 Qc5 21. Rfe1 Rxe1+ 22. Rxe1 Nxd5 (22... Nd7 $1 {This move goes more in the spirit of Black's strategy, fighting against the bad bishop on f3.} 23. Re3 (23. Re7 $6 Bxc3 24. Qxc3 (24. Rxd7 Qb5 $17 {[%csl Ra3,Ga4,Rb2][%cal Gb5b2,Gb5d7,Ga4a1]}) 24... Qxc3 25. bxc3 Nc5 $17 {[%cal Gg8f8]}) 23... Bxc3 (23... Bd4 24. Rd3) 24. Rxc3 Qb6 25. Rc7 Nc5 26. Re7 Kf8 27. Re3 Re8 $15) 23. Bxd5 Qxd5 24. Bxg7 Kxg7 25. Qc3+ Kg8 26. Re7 $13 {0-1 Mekhitarian,K (2563)-Guseinov,G (2666)/chess.com INT 2020} *

