{In this game we will see a new idea. White is playing with 0-0-0.} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. f3 Nc6 6. c4 g6 7. Nc3 Bg7 8. Be3 O-O 9. Qd2 Bd7 10. Be2 Nxd4 11. Bxd4 Bc6 (11... a5 {I believe that this is the best move order because after 0-0-0.Black is not playing Bc6 but on e6} 12. O-O-O a4 13. a3 Qa5 14. g4 Be6 {[%cal Rf8c8,Rf6d7]}) 12. O-O-O a5 (12... Qa5 {also doesn't help much} 13. Kb1 Rfc8 14. g4 a6 15. h4 b5 16. h5 bxc4 17. Bxc4 $16) (12... a6 {the counterplay looks too slow} 13. g4 b5 14. h4 b4 15. Nd5 $18) 13. Kb1 Nd7 14. h4 Bxd4 15. Qxd4 Qb6 16. Qd2 h5 (16... a4 17. a3 $16) 17. g4 Nf6 18. gxh5 Nxh5 19. Nd5 Bxd5 20. exd5 Kg7 21. Rhg1 Rh8 22. f4 Nf6 23. f5 Rh6 24. Bd3 Qd4 25. fxg6 fxg6 26. Rde1 Re8 27. Qc2 Ng4 28. a3 Ne5 29. Be4 Rf8 30. h5 Rf2 31. Qc1 Nxc4 32. Bc2 Nd2+ 33. Ka1 b5 34. Rxe7+ Kf8 35. Rc7 Rf3 36. Ka2 Qxd5+ 37. b3 Qd4 38. hxg6 Qe3 39. g7+ Ke8 40. Rc8+ Kd7 41. g8=Q 1-0

